        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=59377&TOPIC_ID=7396&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Gears+that+reduce+downtime&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Thus, if you lich down 500 hitpoints in a fight, it doesn't MATTER if your max hp is 2000, 1500, or 1000. You still have to spend the same amount of mana to get your health back up.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote><BR>That's not exactly true, xzzy.  The question is, <i>how often</i> you have to spend the mana to get your health back up.</P><P>The higher your HP, the less often you have to recharge the HP batteries with BoD (our least efficient DoT).  If you have low HP, you are having to use BoD to stay above a safety margin on health almost every other kill, and a percentage of the tapped HP goes wasted at max HP.  This means an extra ~150 mana wasted per mob, compared to having much higher HP level, in which you might BoD every 3rd or 4th mob.  </P><P>So, due to the very tight range between full health and dangerously low, a necro with 1000 HP is wasting mana tap-killing the mob, instead of using the more efficient DoT's like IB, Splurt, etc....  Depending on where you hunt, this range is further tightened by the likelihood of taking some damage (like the HS entrance).</P><P>In answer to the original query by Carrigan, the biggest impact on HP/Mana regen aside from spells & items with regen effects, is your level.  The 1 pt. per tick rule increases noticeably between 50-60.</P><P></P><P>Brujo Cuatlique<BR>56th Defiler<BR>Dark Advocates<BR>Test Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
