        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Ya have to love these kind of discussions.  Well here is my take on this.  I do not have those uber regin items and I'm not an iksar.  I feel its mostly just what people are more comfortable with.  I have several items giveing me hps, and also many that give mana and int.  I am currently at 209 int and have about 250 to 300 in mana items on and also am wearing hps stuff also.  Now for my take on more hps is better is mainly because I can actually stay liching longer.  Now being in lich longer sure I have to still use same amount of mana to cast bod BUT here is the catch.  If you are casting bod on every fight while pulling nonstop.  Well your haveing to use way to much mana in the first place and that is where the being efficiant comes in to play.  Over a longer period of time pulling nonstop which a necro can do better than any other.  I use less mana by not haveing to cast BOD to keep my health up.  Now I know this also depends on mobs your killing also.  I made my dicision based on killing same mob around lvl 40 and pulling nonstop.  If you sit with a caculater and add up what spells your using and what second necro is using that has more hps, then you will actually find he uses less mana than the other and also can keep pulling for longer periods of time before maybe needing to take a break.  Maybe a bit of rambling but I enjoy good topics to talk about.</P><P>Faiena Soulseeker,<BR>55 Defiler of Povar,<BR>Valor of Virtopia.</P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
